    dc:description "FIGURE 8 Diaulota uenoi. A, habitus, male; B, ditto, female; C, labium; D, mentum; E, median lode of aedeagus, lateral view; F, internal structure of median lobe, dorsal view; G, ditto, ventral view; H, spermatheca. Scale bars: 1.0 mm for A, B; 0.1 mm for C–H. Abbreviation: as, apical sclerite; su, suspensonia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10361594/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10361598>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9 Holotype of Diaulota uenoi. A, dissected body parts and label on slide glass; B, labrum; C, median lobe, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for A & B." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10361598/files/figure.png" ;
